<p>
The area <em>A</em> of an equilateral triangle is equal to the square root =
of 3 divided by 4, times the length of the sides <em>a</em> squared.
</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_2_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-con=
