<h3 id=3D"idx_how_to_calculate_the_perimeter_of_a_hexagon">How to Calculate=
 the Perimeter of a Hexagon</h3>
<p>
Since a regular hexagon has six equal sides, to <a href=3D"https://www.inch=
calculator.com/perimeter-calculator/" data-google-interstitial=3D"false">fi=
nd the perimeter</a>, you can multiply the length of the sides by 6.
</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_3_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-con=
tent adthrive-content-3 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div=
>
<div class=3D"latex latex--mh3 latex--left latex--mode-display latex--bg-gr=
ey loaded" data-latex=3D"" data-latex-alignment=3D"left" data-latex-mode=3D=
"display"><span class=3D"katex-display fleqn"><span class=3D"katex"><span c=
