6444em;"></span><span class=3D"mord">6</span><span class=3D"mord mathnormal=
">a</span></span></span></span></span></div>
<p>
The perimeter <em>P</em> of a hexagon is equal to 6 times the length of the=
 sides <em>a</em>.
</p>
<h3 id=3D"idx_how_to_calculate_the_diagonals_of_a_hexagon">How to Calculate=
 the Diagonals of a Hexagon</h3>
<p>
In a regular hexagon:
</p>
<ul>
<li>A short diagonal connects two non-adjacent vertices that have one verte=
x between them.</li>
<li>A long diagonal connects two non-adjacent vertices with two vertices be=
tween them.</li>
</ul>
<p>
You can calculate the length of the diagonals using a few formulas.
</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_4_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-con=
tent adthrive-content-4 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div=
>
