</p>
<p>=E2=80=8B</p>
<h3 id=3D"idx_how_to_calculate_the_circumradius_and_inradius_of_a_hexagon">=
How to Calculate the Circumradius and Inradius of a Hexagon</h3>
<p>
Just like a <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/triangle-calculator/"=
 data-google-interstitial=3D"false">triangle</a> or <a href=3D"https://www.=
inchcalculator.com/octagon-calculator/" data-google-interstitial=3D"false">=
octagon</a>, a hexagon has a circumradius and an inradius.
</p>
<p>
The <em>circumradius</em> of a hexagon is the radius of the circumscribed c=
ircle that passes through all the vertices of the hexagon. The circumradius=
 is often referred to as just the <em>radius</em>.
</p>
<p>
The <em>inradius</em>, or the <em>apothem</em>, of a hexagon is the perpend=
icular distance from the center of the hexagon to one of its sides. In a re=
gular hexagon, this is also the height of one of the equilateral triangles =
when split.
</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_6_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-con=
tent adthrive-content-6 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div=
>
<div class=3D"article-thumbnail article-thumbnail-width-80">
<img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.=
com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/hexagon-radius-apothem.png" alt=3D"Graphic s=
howing the circumradius and inradius of a hexagon." width=3D"1280" height=
=3D"854" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-13503">
</div>
<p>
You can calculate the circumradius and apothem using a few formulas.
